@kpayson64 I realize I haven't enumerated all my arguments for why this is the lesser of many, many evils, but that's because the remainder of them are conditional on the alternative approaches and why those approaches would fail.

For example, we have a custom command in `grpcio-tools` which ought to be tested. We can't test that command unless we've built `grpcio-tools`, and we can't build that command until we've installed `grpcio-tools`. So unless we want to be dynamically generating new projects in our tests (maybe we do, but that's a paper cut among many we already have), we need a new project _anyway_ just to test the `grpcio-tools` custom command.

... And I have other things but they're all conditional and I haven't written them down, so, I'unno, feel free to bug me in meat-space about it.
